# PayVault System Redesign — Merchant Portal

## Problem Statement

Currently, PayVault has **two actors** but only **one panel**:

| Actor | Has Panel? | Current Reality |
|-------|-----------|-----------------|
| **Admin** (Platform Operator) | ✅ Admin Panel | Manages everything: services, keys, IPN endpoints, refunds, config |
| **Merchant** (Developer Integrating) | ❌ None | Must ask admin for every change — can't self-manage webhooks, URLs, keys |

This is not how a **real payment gateway** works. Stripe, Razorpay, SSLCommerz — they all have a **merchant dashboard** where the integrating developer can:
- Manage webhooks themselves
- Set default callback URLs
- View their own transactions and revenue
- Rotate API keys
- Test webhook delivery
- Submit and track refund requests

