## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Role Boundary Decision**: The plan separates Admin (platform) from Merchant (integrator) clearly. The merchant can NEVER access another service's data, change gateway config, or approve refunds. If you want merchants to have any admin-level capabilities, let me know.

> [!WARNING]
> **Database Migration**: This adds a new `merchant_users` table and a `merchant_sessions` table. Existing data is not affected, but the migration must run against the live DB.

---

## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **1. Merchant Self-Registration?** Should merchants be able to sign up themselves at `/merchant/register`, or should the admin create merchant accounts and send invite links? I recommend **admin-creates-and-invites** for a B2B payment gateway — you don't want random people creating merchant accounts.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **2. Multi-User per Service?** Should a single service (e.g., "E-commerce App") have multiple merchant users (e.g., CTO and backend dev)? I recommend **yes, with roles** (owner / developer / viewer) but this adds complexity. We can start with **one merchant user per service** and expand later.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **3. Fee / Commission Tracking?** Real payment gateways charge fees. Should we add a `commission_rate` field to services for future billing? Not implementing now, but the schema decision affects the future.

