### Backend — Rust API

#### [NEW] `src/api/merchant/` — New module tree

```
src/api/merchant/
├── mod.rs          # Module declaration
├── auth.rs         # Login/logout, password change
├── dashboard.rs    # Service-scoped metrics
├── webhooks.rs     # CRUD for IPN endpoints
├── settings.rs     # Default URLs, service profile
├── keys.rs         # View keys, rotate, reveal
├── transactions.rs # List/search own transactions
├── refunds.rs      # Submit/view own refunds
└── deliveries.rs   # View webhook delivery logs, test ping
```

#### [NEW] `src/api/middleware/merchant_auth.rs`

Session-based auth (same pattern as admin), but resolves to:
```rust
pub struct AuthenticatedMerchant {
    pub merchant_user_id: Uuid,
    pub service_id: Uuid,   // The service this merchant owns
    pub role: String,       // "owner" | "developer" | "viewer"
}
```

**Every merchant endpoint** uses `service_id` from the session — merchants can NEVER access another service's data.

#### [NEW] `src/db/merchants.rs`

CRUD for `merchant_users` and `merchant_sessions`.

#### [MODIFY] `src/main.rs`

Add new route scope:
```rust
// Merchant API (session auth)
.service(
    web::scope("/api/merchant")
        .configure(api::merchant::auth::routes)
        .service(
            web::scope("")
                .wrap(api::middleware::merchant_auth::MerchantAuthMiddleware)
                .configure(api::merchant::dashboard::routes)
                .configure(api::merchant::webhooks::routes)
                .configure(api::merchant::settings::routes)
                .configure(api::merchant::keys::routes)
                .configure(api::merchant::transactions::routes)
                .configure(api::merchant::refunds::routes)
                .configure(api::merchant::deliveries::routes)
        )
)
// Merchant SPA
.service(
    web::resource("/merchant/{tail:.*}")
        .route(web::get().to(serve_merchant_spa))
)
```

#### [MODIFY] `src/api/admin/services.rs`

Add endpoint to **create a merchant account** when creating a service:
- `POST /api/admin/merchants` — create merchant user, send credentials
- `GET /api/admin/merchants` — list all merchant users
- `PATCH /api/admin/merchants/{id}` — deactivate, reset password

