## What This Enables (Developer Workflow)

```
1. Admin creates service "my-ecommerce" in admin panel
2. Admin creates merchant account (dev@company.com) linked to service
3. Developer logs into /merchant with their credentials
4. Developer sets:
   - success_url: https://shop.com/payment/success
   - fail_url: https://shop.com/payment/failed
   - cancel_url: https://shop.com/payment/cancelled
5. Developer creates webhook:
   - URL: https://shop.com/api/payvault-webhook
   - Events: payment.success, payment.failed, refund.completed
6. Developer generates API key and copies it
7. Developer integrates using /docs examples
8. Developer sends a test webhook to verify endpoint works
9. Developer monitors transaction history and webhook deliveries
10. If refund needed, developer submits refund request → admin approves
```

